    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-11-27T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-11-27T18:00:00-05:00" n="315"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d315">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.77/231a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Vladivostok</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CJK1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caldwell</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-11-27T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 27, 1917, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Following is for <persName corresp="#p_SJF1">Stevens</persName> from <persName
                        corresp="#p_WD1">Daniel Willard</persName>: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Yours advising you will leave shortly for United States. Please do not
                            leave Vladivostok until <persName corresp="#p_ECH1">Emerson</persName>
                            arrives and until you have heard further from me. <persName
                                corresp="#p_ECH1">Emerson</persName> now at Honolulu; should reach
                            Vladivostok early in December on transport <persName corresp="#p_MTG1">
                                <hi rend="italic">Thomas</hi>
                            </persName>. Am hopeful things will develop much better than you expect.
                            Splendid work you have done is greatly appreciated, but it is not
                            finished.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_SJF1">Stevens</persName> is reported at Harbin.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
